# Netlify Deployment Configuration

## Environment Variables for Production

# For Netlify deployment, add these environment variables in your Netlify dashboard:

### Database Configuration (Optional - for full dynamic features)
# DATABASE_URL="your-production-database-url"

### Authentication (Optional - for admin features)
# NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-nextauth-secret-key"
# NEXTAUTH_URL="https://your-site-name.netlify.app"

### Admin Credentials (Optional)
# ADMIN_EMAIL="admin@krishnacare.com"
# ADMIN_PASSWORD="your-secure-password"

## Notes:
# - The site will work without these variables using static fallback data
# - Add these variables in Netlify Dashboard > Site Settings > Environment Variables
# - For database, consider using services like:
#   - Neon (PostgreSQL)
#   - PlanetScale (MySQL)
#   - Railway (PostgreSQL)
#   - Supabase (PostgreSQL)

## Static Content Works Without Database:
# - Blog posts will use static data from /src/lib/staticData.ts
# - Gallery will use images from /public/images/gallery/
# - Contact form will still work via API
# - All basic website functionality is preserved